        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 2:40PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 240 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms capable of producing microbursts extending from 6
miles east of Briggsdale to 5 miles southwest of Westplains, or
extending from 31 miles northeast of Greeley to 22 miles northwest
of Sterling, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
New Raymer, Stoneham, Keota, Jackson Reservoir, Pawnee Pass,
Briggsdale and Buckingham.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
